-- Hungary’s Orban Asked to Name Presidential Candidate, MTI Says
-- B y   E d i t h   B a l a z s
-- 2012-04-03T05:58:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-03/hungary-s-orban-asked-to-name-presidential-candidate-mti-says.html
Hungary ’s ruling coalition asked
Prime Minister  Viktor Orban  to nominate a presidential candidate
on April 16 to replace  Pal Schmitt , who resigned, state news
service MTI reported, citing Janos Lazar, who heads the ruling
Fidesz party’s parliamentary group.  Following Schmitt’s resignation amid a plagiarism scandal,
Hungary needs a new president as soon as possible, MTI cited
Lazar as saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Edith Balazs in Budapest at 
 ebalazs1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at 
 jagomez@bloomberg.net  